{"id":"sxAct-45e3","title":"Python API: expose xCoba coordinate functions","description":"xact-py api.py is missing the entire xCoba surface that exists in sxact's julia_stub and in XTensor.jl. Missing Python bindings: def_basis!, def_chart!, SetBasisChange, ChangeBasis, GetJacobian, BasisChangeQ, SetComponents, GetComponents, ComponentValue, CTensorQ, ToBasis, FromBasis, TraceBasisDummy, Christoffel. Users who need coordinate components (Schwarzschild metric components, geodesic equations) have no Python path — they must drop to Julia or use sxact's TOML runner. This blocks using xact-py as the primary interface for GR calculations.

Why: feature parity vs Wolfram xAct Python API. Every xCoba function in the Julia engine must be callable from Python.
How to apply: implement xact.def_basis(), xact.def_chart(), xact.set_basis_change(), xact.change_basis(), xact.get_jacobian(), xact.basis_change_q(), xact.set_components(), xact.get_components(), xact.component_value(), xact.ctensor_q(), xact.to_basis(), xact.from_basis(), xact.trace_basis_dummy(), xact.christoffel() in api.py and export from __init__.py.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"saxa.kile@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-03-17T20:23:27Z","created_by":"sashakile","updated_at":"2026-03-17T20:23:27Z"}

{"id":"sxAct-jpj4","title":"Python API: export covd() and CovDExpr for typed covariant derivative expressions","description":"CovDExpr exists in xact/expr.py but is not exported from xact/__init__.py, and there is no covd() factory function in the Python public API. In Julia, covd(:CD) returns a CovDHead which supports CD[-a](phi[]) syntax. Python users cannot build typed covariant derivative expressions. This is a gap in the TExpr layer completeness.

Why: TExpr is done for tensors but incomplete for covariant derivatives in Python.
How to apply: add covd() function to expr.py (parallel to tensor()), export CovDExpr and covd from __init__.py. Also add CovDHead to exports. Tests: add to tests/unit/test_texpr.py following the existing pattern.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"saxa.kile@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-03-17T20:23:34Z","created_by":"sashakile","updated_at":"2026-03-17T20:23:34Z"}

{"id":"sxAct-salq","title":"Python API: expose xTras utility functions","description":"xact-py is missing the xTras utility layer that exists in XTensor.jl and sxact's julia_stub. Missing: CollectTensors, AllContractions, SymmetryOf, MakeTraceFree. These are useful for intermediate calculations and needed for feature parity.

Why: parity with Julia API and sxact action vocabulary.
How to apply: add xact.collect_tensors(), xact.all_contractions(), xact.symmetry_of(), xact.make_trace_free() to api.py.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"saxa.kile@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-03-17T20:23:31Z","created_by":"sashakile","updated_at":"2026-03-17T20:23:31Z"}

